to change the colour of the output text

write-host "hello-world" -ForegroundColor red
=======================
passing a value to a variable

$x=5
$y=6
$x+$y will we get the output of the sum of the two variables
===========================
passing the values using array and calling those values using foreach block

$names=@("chandra","sekhar","dimpu","cc","adc")

foreach ($name in $names){

    write-host "name is $name"
}

output:
name is chandra
name is sekhar
name is dimpu
name is cc
name is adc
------------
using two arrays
$names=@("chandra","sekhar","dimpu","cc","adc")
$locations=@("Hyd","sec","chirala","meenakshi","FB")

for ($i=0; $i -lt $names.Length; $i++){

    write-host "my name is $($names[$i]) and i am from $($locations[$i])"
}

output:

my name is chandra and i am from Hyd
my name is sekhar and i am from sec
my name is dimpu and i am from chirala
my name is cc and i am from meenakshi
========================
taking input from the user

$num= read-host "enter a number"
write-host "user input num is $num"
output:
enter a number: 10
user input num is 10
=====================
Out-File command is used to store the output into a file

$number | Out-File ".\sam.txt" -Append (in double quotes mention file name/ file path)

the above command will take the output of $number as input and append that to sam.txt file
